Jun 6 2008 	Perfect place to stay in London	Lovely old building, excellent location (walking distance from a major tube stop), on a quiet street, near many restaurants and other amenities, and the price can't be beat. But most importantly, the owners and staff are some of the nicest people you're likely to meet.I stayed here in 2003 for all of the above reasons, plus it advertised &quot;absolutely no smoking.&quot; When I had the opportunity to return to London, I did not hesitate to call Merlyn Court.Breakfast is a simple affair, usually cereal and toast with tea or coffee. (They stopped serving hot breakfasts when their cook retired after 20 years.) There is no lift, so be prepared for stairs. They have singles, queens/doubles, triples, and quads, so they can accommodate every situation. Bring your own radio, and enjoy the TV lounge downstairs. Please don't expect five-star amenities, but if you're looking for a clean, comfortable, quiet stay that won't bankrupt you, this is the only option.P.S. Although not advertised, I could access wireless Internet throughout most of the building.	
