Oct 16 2007 	Low Cost Motel near Central London	The Merlyn Court hotel fills a specific niche: it's a low cost, clean motel near downtown London and the tube. For those people seeking inexpensive, no frills lodging in London - it works well. Our experience with the motel was fine. Our flight got in early in the morning, and they were nice enough to allow us to check in early. The room was clean, and relatively quiet. The only noises we heard were doors banging at night, but given the age of the building this is understandable. Facilities were en suite, and while small were functional.This hotel does not offer many amenities. Basically, you get a small room and a bed - not much else is included. We ended up buying our own travel alarm clock as there wasn't one in the room. There are no TV's in the room. There is a light breakfast, but it is served from 8-9. We were early risers, so were always gone before breakfast. Would I reccomend this place to other people? Yes - but I would make sure the people understood that this place is very basic. If you are expecting services and room features like a traditional hotel would have - I would have to encourage you to look elsewhere.	
