Jun 8 2006	Absolutely wonderful hotel for the budget traveler!	In total, I spent about 2 weeks at this hotel. I consider this little place to be a lucky find. If you're just looking for a comfortable, decent, and clean place for you to lay down your head at night, this is your sort of hotel. If, however, you want a bit more frill, this isn't for you. For example, the rooms do not have a television set in them. However, there is a lounge if you wish to watch tv. I traveled alone and was on a budget, so I picked the single with a shared bathroom. I figured that I could put the difference I would save from not getting an ensuite to better use... doing something fun or buying something nice. I have to admit, I did have concerns before leaving for my trip. I was a little worried, as I was traveling alone, if perhaps sharing a bathroom would be a bit unsafe. In that... perhaps I would be accosted during the night on my way to the bathroom. I envisioned all sorts of terrible predicaments. And now... I can tell you that I am delighted that I decided to save the cash. I stayed there nearly 2 weeks and only encountered someone using the bathroom, twice. The bathroom was always clean and both rooms I had (I stayed there for two periods) were quite close to the bathroom (which is great when you feel sloppy and gross in the morning and are eager to get to the shower before anyone has a chance to spot what you look like after you first awake!). So... the money you save makes this hotel attractive. I got a single without a bathroom, for only 40 pounds a night.  Another thing that makes this hotel really attractive is the location!!! Walk down the street and make a right and there is Earls Court Tube Station! This station is within zones 1 and 2, the most popular zones in London. The Earls Court line seems to be an integral one as it has connections to the District, Circle, and Piccadilly lines. All lines that seem to be very popular. Also, Earls Court has a little of everything you need to feel as comfortable as you would be at home. Drugstore, convenience stores, supermarkets, laundromats, Internet cafes, coffee shops... everything! Well, if I haven't sold you on this place, yet... I would also like to add that the people who work at the hotel, are very friendly. Especially Luciana. On my very last day in London, I was preparing to leave with a very heavy heart. Also, I had a dilemma. I had a flight out of Heathrow very late in the evening and didn't know what to do with myself until then, with all my luggage in tow. I need not have worried as when I was checking out, Luciana flat out offered to watch my luggage for me as I soaked in a last few hours of London. I thought that was really sweet and considerate of her. The hotel workers are just really helpful and seem to care that you are enjoying your trip. Overall: Great budget hotel and I would love to go back there.	
